EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT making an appropriation to the Department of Education
for the purpose of awarding grants of money to school
districts or institutions within the Nevada System of
Higher Education for programs of dual credit; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. There is hereby appropriated from the State
2 General Fund to the Department of Education the sum of
3 $15,000,000 for the purpose of awarding grants of money in
4 accordance with this section to school districts and institutions
5 within the Nevada System of Higher Education for programs of dual
6 credit at public schools in this State.
7 2. The Department shall allocate the money appropriated by
8 subsection 1 to school districts and institutions within the System to
9 cover the cost of student fees and instructional materials for pupils
10 enrolled in new and existing dual credit programs who are able to
11 demonstrate financial or other hardship, including, without
12 limitation:
13 (a) Pupils who, once enrolled in a postsecondary educational
14 institution, will be first-generation college students;
15 (b) Pupils from historically underserved communities; or
16 (c) Pupils who either directly receive or are members of a
17 household that receives public assistance, as defined in
-
