1 NRS 422A.065, or who are eligible for free or reduced-price
2 lunches pursuant to 42 U.S.C. §§ 1751 et seq.
3 3. A school district or institution within the System may
4 expend money allocated pursuant to subsection 2 on behalf of the
5 same pupil more than once, to cover the cost of student fees and
6 instructional materials for multiple classes or semesters, or at
7 multiple institutions.
8 4. In allocating the money appropriated by subsection 1, the
9 Department shall not:
10 (a) Impose geographic limitations on where a program of dual
11 credit may be offered or limit whether instruction is offered at an
12 institution within the System, at a high school or online;
13 (b) Impose limitations on the subject area of courses offered in a
14 program of dual credit; or
15 (c) Interfere with the choice of instructor for a dual credit course
16 made by an institution within the System.
17 5. Upon acceptance of the money appropriated by subsection 1,
18 a school district or institution within the System, as applicable,
19 agrees to:
20 (a) Prepare and transmit a report to the Interim Finance
21 Committee on or before December 18, 2026, that describes, from
22 the date on which the money was received by the school district or
23 institution within the System through December 1, 2026:
24 (1) Each expenditure made from the money appropriated by
25 subsection 1;
26 (2) The number of pupils enrolled in dual credit programs for
27 whom money appropriated by subsection 1 was expended; and
28 (3) For pupils for whom money appropriated by subsection 1
29 was expended, high school graduation rates and rates of
30 matriculation into institutions within the System;
31 (b) Prepare and transmit a final report to the Interim Finance
32 Committee on or before September 17, 2027, that describes, from
33 the date on which the money was received by the school district or
34 institution within the System through June 30, 2027:
35 (1) Each expenditure made from the money appropriated by
36 subsection 1;
37 (2) The number of pupils enrolled in dual credit programs for
38 whom money appropriated by subsection 1 was expended; and
39 (3) For pupils for whom money appropriated by subsection 1
40 was expended, high school graduation rates and rates of
41 matriculation into institutions within the System; and
42 (c) Prepare the reports required pursuant to this subsection in a
43 manner that complies with the provisions of the Family Educational
44 Rights and Privacy Act of 1974, 20 U.S.C. § 1232g.
